article.headline: Mississippi St. 81, McNeese State 58
article.story:
STARKVILLE, Miss. (AP) -- Seneca Anderson and Tan White scored 18
points apiece as Mississippi State beat McNeese State 81-58 on
Saturday night.

Rebecca Kates added 14 points for the Lady Bulldogs (5-4).

No player scored in double figures for McNeese State (2-7).
Clarissa Clark, Regina Spivey and Marquita Williams had nine points
each.

Mississippi State never trailed in the game. The Lady Bulldogs
were 31-for-63 from the field.

McNeese State shot 24-for-52 from the field.

Mississippi State outrebounded McNeese State 38-25, led by
Anderson, who had six.

The Lady Bulldogs had 11 steals and scored 32 points off
turnovers.
